78
00:03:55,902 --> 00:04:01,086
you think about the player, you think about, okay, the player has to catch up, flank, or run away,

79
00:04:01,807 --> 00:04:07,430
the player has to take cover, or move really fast, or strafe to break line of sight, or break awareness of the AI,

80
00:04:08,011 --> 00:04:11,093
or the player has to run and gun, or get close up, or snipe from a distance,

81
00:04:11,853 --> 00:04:14,455
and now you can combine the mechanics from the player's perspective and say,

82
00:04:14,475 --> 00:04:19,399
okay, I want to create an AI that you have to flank, then you have to take cover and snipe from the side,

83
00:04:19,439 --> 00:04:24,182
and that might be an enemy that's really strong at the front, or really strong in close range.

84
00:04:25,252 --> 00:04:29,181
Or you say, okay, I want to catch up with the AI, be really fast and run and gun it down.

85
00:04:29,462 --> 00:04:33,912
That might be an AI that is harder and harder over time and that you have to take out fast.

86
00:04:35,010 --> 00:04:39,032
This helps you, this helps you to really understand what the player is doing, right?

87
00:04:39,072 --> 00:04:43,996
Whether the experience is unique for the player and whether one AI plays differently than

88
